{
    "id": "physicsutil",
    "lang": "en-us",
    "name": "PhysicsUtil",
    "description": "Make objects move with real physics: push them with forces, set their speed, spin them, and shoot rays to detect what's in front of them.",
    "link": "/docs/uniscript/en-us/physicsutil",
    "tags": [
        "uniscript",
        "physicsutil",
        "physics",
        "force",
        "velocity",
        "raycast"
    ],
    "previous": {
        "name": "ColliderUtil",
        "link": "/docs/uniscript/en-us/colliderutil"
    },
    "next": {
        "name": "CameraUtil",
        "link": "/docs/uniscript/en-us/camerautil"
    },
    "content": [
        {
            "id": "block-001",
            "tag": "h1",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "text": "PhysicsUtil"
        },
        {
            "id": "block-002",
            "tag": "p",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "text": "`PhysicsUtil` makes objects behave like real-world things — they can be pushed, fall under gravity, bounce, roll, and spin. It's the right tool for balls, projectiles, crates, and anything that should move physically. It also includes **raycasting**: shooting an invisible ray to detect what an object is looking at."
        },
        {
            "id": "block-003",
            "tag": "h2",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "text": "Step 1 — Give the object physics"
        },
        {
            "id": "block-004",
            "tag": "p",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "text": "Before an object can be pushed or fall, it needs a physics body. Add one once with `AddPhysics`:"
        },
        {
            "id": "block-005",
            "tag": "code",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "lines": [
                "class Ball",
                "{",
                "    void OnInit()",
                "    {",
                "        PhysicsUtil.AddPhysics(this);   // now it can move and fall",
                "    }",
                "}"
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "block-006",
            "tag": "h2",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "text": "Setting and reading speed"
        },
        {
            "id": "block-007",
            "tag": "p",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "text": "**Velocity** is an object's speed and direction combined, as a `vector3`. Setting it directly is the simplest way to control movement."
        },
        {
            "id": "block-008",
            "tag": "table",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "headers": [
                "Method",
                "What it does"
            ],
            "rows": [
                ["`SetVelocity(this, velocity)`", "Sets the object's exact speed and direction."],
                ["`GetVelocity(this)`", "Reads the current speed and direction — e.g. to check if it's falling."]
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "block-009",
            "tag": "code",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "lines": [
                "// Launch the ball forward at 10 units/second.",
                "PhysicsUtil.SetVelocity(this, VectorUtil.New(0.0, 0.0, 10.0));"
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "block-010",
            "tag": "h2",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "text": "Pushing with forces"
        },
        {
            "id": "block-011",
            "tag": "p",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "text": "`AddForce` pushes an object instead of setting its speed outright — which feels more natural for jumps, explosions, and wind. The last parameter, the **force mode**, decides how the push is applied:"
        },
        {
            "id": "block-012",
            "tag": "table",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "headers": [
                "Mode",
                "Name",
                "Use for"
            ],
            "rows": [
                ["`0`", "Acceleration", "A steady push that ignores how heavy the object is."],
                ["`1`", "Force", "A steady push affected by weight (the everyday choice for continuous push)."],
                ["`2`", "Impulse", "A sudden, one-off kick affected by weight — jumps, hits, explosions."],
                ["`3`", "VelocityChange", "A sudden kick that ignores weight — instant, consistent speed changes."]
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "block-013",
            "tag": "code",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "lines": [
                "// An instant upward jump (Impulse = 2).",
                "PhysicsUtil.AddForce(this, 0.0, 8.0, 0.0, 2);",
                "",
                "// The same push using a vector.",
                "vector3 jump = VectorUtil.New(0.0, 8.0, 0.0);",
                "PhysicsUtil.AddForce(this, jump, 2);"
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "block-014",
            "tag": "h2",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "text": "Spinning objects"
        },
        {
            "id": "block-015",
            "tag": "p",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "text": "**Torque** is a twisting push that makes an object rotate. It works just like force, including the same mode numbers."
        },
        {
            "id": "block-016",
            "tag": "table",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "headers": [
                "Method",
                "What it does"
            ],
            "rows": [
                ["`AddTorque(this, x, y, z, mode)`", "Applies a spinning push."],
                ["`AddTorque(this, vector, mode)`", "Same, using a `vector3`."],
                ["`SetAngularVelocity(this, velocity)` / `GetAngularVelocity(this)`", "Set or read how fast the object is spinning."],
                ["`SetCenterOfMass(this, center)`", "Moves the object's balance point — affects how it tips and spins."]
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "block-017",
            "tag": "h2",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "text": "Moving platforms"
        },
        {
            "id": "block-018",
            "tag": "p",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "text": "`AddMovingPlatform(this)` marks an object as a moving platform so characters standing on it are carried along correctly as it moves."
        },
        {
            "id": "block-019",
            "tag": "h2",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "text": "Raycasting — detecting what's ahead"
        },
        {
            "id": "block-020",
            "tag": "p",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "text": "A **raycast** shoots an invisible line from a point in a direction and reports the first thing it hits. It's how you check what's under a character (ground detection), what a gun is aimed at, or whether there's a wall ahead."
        },
        {
            "id": "block-021",
            "tag": "p",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "text": "`Raycast` returns a [Dictionary](/docs/uniscript/en-us/dictionaryutil) describing the hit, or nothing if the ray hit empty space. The dictionary holds these keys:"
        },
        {
            "id": "block-022",
            "tag": "table",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "headers": [
                "Key",
                "What it holds"
            ],
            "rows": [
                ["`\"point\"`", "The exact spot where the ray hit (a `vector3`)."],
                ["`\"normal\"`", "The direction the hit surface faces."],
                ["`\"other\"`", "The script of the object that was hit — so you can act on it."]
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "block-023",
            "tag": "code",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "lines": [
                "// Shoot a ray straight down to find the ground, up to 5 units away.",
                "vector3 from = UniObjectUtil.GetWorldPosition(this);",
                "Dictionary hit = PhysicsUtil.Raycast(from, VectorUtil.Down(), 5.0);",
                "",
                "if (hit != null)",
                "{",
                "    vector3 groundPoint = DictionaryUtil.Get(hit, \"point\");",
                "    Debug.Log(\"Ground found!\");",
                "}"
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "block-024",
            "tag": "p",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "text": "You can also limit a ray to only notice objects with a certain **tag** (or list of tags), and `RaycastAll` reports every object along the line instead of just the first:"
        },
        {
            "id": "block-025",
            "tag": "table",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "headers": [
                "Method",
                "What it does"
            ],
            "rows": [
                ["`Raycast(from, direction, distance)`", "First object hit."],
                ["`Raycast(from, direction, distance, tag)`", "First object hit that has this tag."],
                ["`Raycast(from, direction, distance, tags)`", "First object hit matching any tag in the list."],
                ["`RaycastAll(...)`", "A list of all objects along the ray (each entry has a `\"valid\"` key plus the same hit keys)."]
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "block-026",
            "tag": "h2",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "text": "Full method reference"
        },
        {
            "id": "block-027",
            "tag": "table",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "headers": [
                "Returns",
                "Method",
                "Parameters"
            ],
            "rows": [
                ["`void`", "`AddPhysics`", "`uniscript`"],
                ["`void`", "`AddForce`", "`uniscript, float x, float y, float z, int mode`"],
                ["`void`", "`AddForce`", "`uniscript, vector3 force, int mode`"],
                ["`vector3`", "`GetVelocity`", "`uniscript`"],
                ["`void`", "`SetVelocity`", "`uniscript, vector3 velocity`"],
                ["`void`", "`AddMovingPlatform`", "`uniscript`"],
                ["`void`", "`AddTorque`", "`uniscript, float x, float y, float z, int mode`"],
                ["`void`", "`AddTorque`", "`uniscript, vector3 force, int mode`"],
                ["`vector3`", "`GetAngularVelocity`", "`uniscript`"],
                ["`void`", "`SetAngularVelocity`", "`uniscript, vector3 velocity`"],
                ["`void`", "`SetCenterOfMass`", "`uniscript, vector3 center`"],
                ["`Dictionary`", "`Raycast`", "`vector3 position, vector3 direction, float maxDistance`"],
                ["`Dictionary`", "`Raycast`", "`vector3 position, vector3 direction, float maxDistance, string tag`"],
                ["`Dictionary`", "`Raycast`", "`vector3 position, vector3 direction, float maxDistance, List tags`"],
                ["`List`", "`RaycastAll`", "`vector3 position, vector3 direction, float maxDistance`"],
                ["`List`", "`RaycastAll`", "`vector3 position, vector3 direction, float maxDistance, string tag`"],
                ["`List`", "`RaycastAll`", "`vector3 position, vector3 direction, float maxDistance, List tags`"]
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "block-028",
            "tag": "warning",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "text": "**Don't add physics to a playable character.** A Character already has its own physics body; adding another makes the two fight and causes janky movement. To move a character, use the movement tools in [CharacterUtil](/docs/uniscript/en-us/characterutil) instead."
        },
        {
            "id": "block-029",
            "tag": "tip",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "text": "Physics moves an object, but it needs a shape to bump into things. Pair `PhysicsUtil` with a collider from [ColliderUtil](/docs/uniscript/en-us/colliderutil)."
        }
    ]
}
